\tab\cf2\ldblquote We sat down on the bench under the big oak tree where we could look across the small lake to the private speedway. It was the warm part of the day and the cars were out in force, at least thirty of them. Even at this \expndtw-3 distance I could see that Jeremiah was pulling his usual stunt of sneaking up \expndtw-1 behind some staid older model, then putting on a jerk of speed and yowling past with deliberately squealing brakes. Two weeks before he had crowded \expndtw0 old Angus off the asphalt altogether, and I had turned off his motor for two \expndtw-12 days.\cf0\expndtw0\par
