\tab\cf2 Good old Matthew. He stayed in the garage most of the day now, but then he was the granddaddy of all positronic-motored cars. Those were the days when blind war veterans, paraplegics and heads of state were the only \expndtw-1 ones who drove automatics. But Samson Harridge was my boss and he was \expndtw0 rich enough to be able to get one. I was his chauffeur at the time.\cf0\par
\tab\cf2 The thought makes me feel old. I can remember when there wasn\rquote t an automobile in the world with brains enough to find its own way home. I chauffeured dead lumps of machines that needed a man\rquote s hand at their controls every minute. Every year machines like that used to kill tens of \expndtw-1 thousands of people.\cf0\expndtw0\par
