\tab\cf2\expndtw-7\ldblquote So they say. So they say. Just the same, you\rquote re sitting right behind the \expndtw-10 wheel in case anything goes wrong.\rdblquote\cf0\expndtw0\par
\tab\cf2\expndtw-9 Funny how you can get to like a car. In no time I was calling it Matthew \expndtw-8 and was spending all my time keeping it polished and humming. A posi\-tronic brain stays in condition best when it\rquote s got control of its chassis at all times, which means it\rquote s worth keeping the gas tank filled so that the motor \expndtw-10 can turn over slowly day and night. After a while, it got so I could tell by the \expndtw-7 sound of the motor how Matthew felt.\cf0\expndtw0\par
