\tab\cf2\expndtw-6 And they don\rquote t talk among themselves only. They talk to the cars and \expndtw-10 buses that come into the Farm on business. How long have they been doing \expndtw-12 that?\cf0\expndtw0\par
\tab\cf2\expndtw-9 They must be understood, too. Gellhorn\rquote s bus understood them, for all it \expndtw-5 hadn\rquote t been on the grounds more than an hour. I can close my eyes and \expndtw-8 bring back that dash along the highway, with our cars flanking the bus on \expndtw-9 either side, clacking their motors at it till it understood, stopped, let me out, \expndtw-8 and ran off with Gellhorn.\cf0\expndtw0\par
\tab\cf2\expndtw-7 Did my cars tell him to kill Gellhorn? Or was that his idea?\cf0\expndtw0\par
\tab\cf2\expndtw-7\i Can \i0 cars have such ideas? The motor designers say no. But they mean \expndtw-10 under ordinary conditions. Have they foreseen \i everything!\rquote\cf0\expndtw0\i0\par
\tab\cf2\expndtw-11 Cars get ill-used, you know.\cf0\expndtw0\par
\tab\cf2\expndtw-6 Some of them enter the Farm and observe. They get told things. They \expndtw-9 find out that cars exist whose motors are never stopped, whom no one ever \expndtw-11 drives, whose every need is supplied.\cf0\expndtw0\par
\tab\cf2\expndtw-6 Then maybe they go out and tell others. Maybe the word is spreading \expndtw-10 quickly. Maybe they\rquote re going to think that the Farm way should be the way \expndtw-4 all over the world. They don\rquote t understand. You couldn\rquote t expect them to \expndtw-8 understand about legacies and the whims of rich men.\cf0\expndtw0\par
\tab\cf2\expndtw-4 There are millions of automatobiles on Earth, tens of millions. If the \expndtw-8 thought gets rooted in them that they\rquote re slaves; that they should do some\-\expndtw-6 thing about it \expndtw67 ...\expndtw0  \expndtw-6 If they begin to think the way Gellhorn\rquote s bus did. . . .\cf0\expndtw0\par
\tab\cf2\expndtw-9 Maybe it won\rquote t be till after my time. And then they\rquote ll have to keep a few \expndtw-7 of us to take care of them, won\rquote t they? They wouldn\rquote t kill us all.\cf0\expndtw0\par
\tab\cf2\expndtw-5 And maybe they would. Maybe they wouldn\rquote t understand about how \expndtw-8 someone would have to care for them. Maybe they won\rquote t wait.\cf0\expndtw0\par
\tab\cf2\expndtw-6 Every morning I wake up and think, Maybe today. . . .\cf0\expndtw0\par
\tab\cf2\expndtw-7 I don\rquote t get as much pleasure out of my cars as I used to. Lately, I notice \expndtw-8 that I\rquote m even beginning to avoid Sally.\cf0\expndtw0\par
