\tab Susan Calvin sat in the chair, silent, eyes restless. A weight dropped, crashed downward; then pounded aside at the last moment under the synchronized thump of a sudden force beam.\par
\tab And a single robot jerked upright and took two steps.\par
\tab And stopped.\par
\tab But Dr. Calvin was upright, and her finger pointed to him sharply. \ldblquote Nestor 10, come here,\rdblquote  she cried, \ldblquote\i come here!\i0  COME HERE!\rdblquote\par
\tab Slowly, reluctantly, the robot took another step forward. The psychologist shouted at the top of her voice, without taking her eyes from the robot, \ldblquote Get every other robot out of this place, somebody. Get them out quickly, and \i keep\i0  them out.\rdblquote\par
\tab Somewhere within reach of her ears there was noise, and the thud of hard feet upon the floor. She did not look away.\par
\tab Nestor 10 -- if it was Nestor 10 -- took another step, and then, under force of her imperious gesture, two more. He was only ten feet away, when he spoke harshly, \ldblquote I have been told to be lost-\rdblquote\par
\tab Another stop. \ldblquote I must not disobey. They have not found me so far -- He would think me a failure -- He told me -- But it\rquote s not so -- I am powerful and intelligent-\rdblquote\par
\tab The words came in spurts.\par
\tab Another step. \ldblquote I know a good deal -- He would think... I mean I\rquote ve been found -- Disgraceful -- Not I -- I am intelligent -- And by just a master... who is weak -- Slow-\rdblquote\par
\tab Another step -- and one metal arm flew out suddenly to her shoulder, and she felt the weight bearing her down. Her throat constricted, and she felt a shriek tear through.\par
\tab Dimly, she heard Nestor 10\rquote s next words, \ldblquote No one must find me. No master-\rdblquote  and the cold metal was against her, and she was sinking under the weight of it.\par
\tab And then a queer, metallic sound, and she was on the ground with an unfelt thump, and a gleaming arm was heavy across her body. It did not move. Nor did Nestor 10, who sprawled beside her.\par
\tab And now faces were bending over her.\par
\tab Gerald Black was gasping, \ldblquote Are you hurt, Dr. Calvin?\rdblquote\par
\tab She shook her head feebly. They pried the arm off her and lifted her gently to her feet, \ldblquote What happened?\rdblquote\par
\tab Black said, \ldblquote I bathed the place in gamma rays for five seconds. We didn\rquote t know what was happening. It wasn\rquote t till the last second that we realized he was attacking you, and then there was no time for anything but a gamma field. He went down in an instant. There wasn\rquote t enough to harm you though. Don\rquote t worry about it.\rdblquote\par
\tab\ldblquote I\rquote m not worried.\rdblquote  She closed her eyes and leaned for a moment upon his shoulder. \ldblquote I don\rquote t think I was attacked exactly. Nestor 10 was simply \i trying\i0  to do so. What was left of the First Law was still holding him back.\rdblquote\par
