\tab But perhaps not all the confidence that Dr. Lanning had remarked upon was present that evening when Byerley\rquote s car parked on the automatic treads leading to the sunken garage, and Byerley himself crossed the path to the front door of his house.\par
\tab The figure in the wheel chair looked up as he entered and smiled. Byerley\rquote s face lit with affection. He crossed over to it.\par
\tab The cripple\rquote s voice was a hoarse, grating whisper that came out of a mouth forever twisted to one side, leering out of a face that was half scar tissue, \ldblquote You\rquote re late, Steve.\rdblquote\par
\tab\ldblquote I know, John, I know. But I\rquote ve been up against a peculiar and interesting trouble today.\rdblquote\par
\tab\ldblquote So?\rdblquote  Neither the torn face nor the destroyed voice could carry expression but there was anxiety in the clear eyes. \ldblquote Nothing you can\rquote t handle?\rdblquote\par
\tab\ldblquote I\rquote m not exactly certain. I may need your help. \i You\rquote re\i0  the brilliant one in the family. Do you want me to take you out into the garden? It\rquote s a beautiful evening.\rdblquote\par
